# Railway Deployment Environment Variables
# Copy these to Railway dashboard → Backend Service → Variables

# ============================================
# REQUIRED - Set these in Railway
# ============================================

# Node Environment (Required)
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000

# Database (Required - Railway auto-provides)
# Use Railway's reference syntax to automatically get the connection string
DATABASE_URL=${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}}

# Redis (Required - Railway auto-provides)  
# Use Railway's reference syntax to automatically get the connection string
REDIS_URL=${{Redis.REDIS_URL}}

# Google Gemini API (Required - Get from https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey)
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here

# JWT Secret (Required - Generate with: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))")
JWT_SECRET=generate-random-32-character-string-here

# Frontend URL (Required - Railway auto-provides)
# This tells the backend where your frontend is hosted
FRONTEND_URL=${{frontend.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}

# CORS Allowed Origins (Required - Railway auto-provides)
# This controls which domains can access your API
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=${{frontend.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL - Defaults are fine for most cases
# ============================================

# Session Configuration
SESSION_DURATION_MINUTES=90

# IRT Configuration
IRT_EASY_THRESHOLD=-0.8
IRT_HARD_THRESHOLD=0.8
MAX_LIKELIHOOD_ITERATIONS=50
CONVERGENCE_CRITERION=0.001

# Database Pool Configuration (Railway defaults are good)
DB_POOL_MIN=2
DB_POOL_MAX=10

# ============================================
# HOW TO USE IN RAILWAY
# ============================================

# 1. Go to Railway Dashboard → Your Project → Backend Service
# 2. Click "Variables" tab
# 3. Copy the REQUIRED variables above
# 4. Replace placeholders:
#    - Keep ${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}} as-is (Railway auto-fills)
#    - Keep ${{Redis.REDIS_URL}} as-is (Railway auto-fills)
#    - Keep ${{frontend.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}} as-is (Railway auto-fills)
#    - Replace GEMINI_API_KEY with your actual key
#    - Replace JWT_SECRET with generated string

# ============================================
# EXAMPLE AFTER DEPLOYMENT
# ============================================
# After Railway deploys, your variables will look like:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:xyz123@postgres.railway.internal:5432/railway
# REDIS_URL=redis://default:abc456@redis.railway.internal:6379
# FRONTEND_URL=https://toeflsimulator.up.railway.app
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://toeflsimulator.up.railway.app
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSy... (your actual key)
# JWT_SECRET=a7f3d9e8b2c4f1a6... (your generated secret)
